Key Match Events: Evan Ferguson returns to lead the line for Ireland.
Finn Azaz makes his competitive debut for the Republic of Ireland.
Nathan Collins mishits a back-pass leading to Joel Pohjanpalo's goal for Finland.
Ireland's disallowed goal due to offside after a VAR check.
Liam Scales scores a header to equalize for Ireland.
Robbie Brady scores the winning goal for Ireland in the 88th minute.
Pre-Game Insights: Heimir Halgrímsson seeks his first win in charge of Ireland.
Finn Azaz will make his competitive debut for the Republic of Ireland.
Evan Ferguson returns to lead the line up front.
Liam Scales replaces Andrew Omobamidele in the defense.
Robbie Brady's presence suggests a back five formation.
Only 15,000 tickets sold for a 36,000-capacity stadium.
1,100 Irish fans present at the Olympic Stadium in Helsinki.
Post-Match Reflections: Ireland comes from behind to earn three points in Helsinki.
Heimir Halgrímsson is off the mark with his first win as Ireland's manager.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Finnish anthem 'Maamme' was performed before the match.
Finnish fans are less optimistic about their national team than the Irish public.
The match was considered a relegation scrap in the Nations League.
RTÉ mentioned that the disallowed goal might have been due to the ball being out of play or Ferguson being offside.
